extended a
pause in fighting in Aleppo,
Syria, for a

04:26.933 --> 04:32.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
third day, to allow people to
receive aid,
that after the U.N. said planned
evacuations

04:32.939 --> 04:38.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the rebel-held east were
halted, due to
a lack of security guarantees
from the warring

04:38.745 --> 04:40.480 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
sides.

04:40.514 --> 04:43.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, addressing a meeting
in Geneva,
the U.N.'s High Commissioner for
Human Rights

04:43.817 --> 04:46.286 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
again denounced Russian and
Syrian airstrikes.

04:46.319 --> 04:48.522 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ZEID BIN RA'AD ZEID AL-HUSSEIN,
United Nations
High Commissioner for Human
Rights: Indiscriminate

04:48.555 --> 04:53.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
airstrikes across the eastern
part of the
city by government forces and
their allies

04:53.627 --> 05:00.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
are responsible for the
overwhelming majority
of civilian casualties, and
these violations

05:00.901 --> 05:02.903 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
constitute war crimes.

05:02.936 --> 05:08.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if knowingly committed as
part of a widespread
or systematic attack directed
against civilians,

05:08.542 --> 05:10.677 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they constitute crimes against
humanity.

05:10.710 --> 05:15.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Separately, the
United Nations
set up a special inquiry today
to investigate

05:15.682 --> 05:18.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
