of Mosul.

05:45.412 --> 05:50.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A passenger train derailed in
the Central
African country of Cameroon
today, killing

05:50.584 --> 05:55.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at least 55 people and injuring
nearly 600
more.

05:55.121 --> 05:59.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some 1,300 people were on board,
more than
twice the normal load.

05:59.893 --> 06:04.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
First-responders struggled to
pull mud-soaked
victims from the wreckage.

06:04.297 --> 06:08.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Heavy rains had caused several
roads in the
area to collapse.

06:08.235 --> 06:14.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, a series
of cyber-attacks
made dozens of popular Web sites
inaccessible

06:14.674 --> 06:18.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today, from Twitter to the music
streaming
site Spotify.

06:18.945 --> 06:23.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The hack targeted the New
Hampshire-based
Internet infrastructure provider
Dyn.

06:23.950 --> 06:29.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attacks were launched from
devices infected
with malware from millions of
I.P. addresses

06:29.823 --> 06:31.491 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
around the world.

06:31.524 --> 06:35.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The FBI is still working to
determine who's
behind the hack.

06:35.729 --> 06:41.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president of the Philippines
has clarified
comments he made yesterday about
a -- quote

06:41.067 --> 06:43.236 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
