off by laying
out the case against this
gentleman, and what

16:07.433 --> 16:09.268 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is his defense?

16:09.302 --> 16:12.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATT APUZZO, The New York Times:
Well, I mean,
what is fascinating is there is
the case that's

16:12.638 --> 16:14.340 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
been brought.

16:14.373 --> 16:20.046 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And the case that's been
brought, as you said,
is, hey, this guy had terabytes,
billions

16:20.079 --> 16:25.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of pages of documents in his
house, in his
shed, in the back seat of his
car, in the

16:25.418 --> 16:29.322 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
trunk of his car, and,
obviously, you're not
supposed to do that.

16:29.355 --> 16:31.224 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, there is that case.

16:31.257 --> 16:34.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But then there is this other
case that's kind
of looming over all this, and
the question

16:34.727 --> 16:45.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is, is he the guy who, not too
long ago, facilitated
the release of NSA documents,
basically for

16:45.371 --> 16:47.874 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ransom, put them up for sale
online?

16:47.907 --> 16:51.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These were hacking tools, the
way the government,
the United States government,
hacks into other

16:51.811 --> 16:53.813 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
countries and businesses and
whatnot?

16:53.846 --> 16:58.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so that's really what's
going on here,
is, there's, OK, he mishandled
classified

16:59.018 --> 16:59.986 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
information.

17:00.019 --> 17:01.754 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He has basically admitted that.

17:01.787 --> 17:04.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But is he the guy, is he part of
some network
that's putting information up
for sale?

17:05.024 --> 17:08.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, this
originally came
about, as you're indicating,
there was this

17:08.227 --> 17:11.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
