who were auctioning
off this software.

17:11.664 --> 17:13.599 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATT APUZZO: Right.

17:13.633 --> 17:16.869 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And is it
correct that investigators
who were looking into that
release and that

17:16.903 --> 17:19.372 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
case, that's how they discovered
Martin?

17:19.405 --> 17:21.140 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MATT APUZZO: Yes.

17:21.173 --> 17:26.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we're told here is that
Martin sort of
popped up on their radar screen
during the

17:26.479 --> 17:31.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
early parts of the investigation
into the
Shadow Brokers' release, and
using some clever

17:31.751 --> 17:37.723 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
forensics and sort of
old-fashioned investigative
skills, were able to identify
Martin.

17:37.757 --> 17:41.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then when they raided his
house, I think
they were stunned to find as
much stuff as

17:41.727 --> 17:42.895 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
