38:11.723 --> 38:13.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MELODI HOEFT: She was
hysterical.

38:13.625 --> 38:17.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LIZZIE O'LEARY: Jordan Hoeft's
loans are serviced
by Navient, which spun off from
Sallie Mae,

38:17.662 --> 38:19.364 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and now owns its student debt
business.

38:19.397 --> 38:22.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is one of the nation's
largest student
debt servicers.

38:22.667 --> 38:25.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The company handles both private
and federal
loans.

38:25.803 --> 38:29.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hoeft's loans are private, not
federal, and
had a high interest rate.

38:29.874 --> 38:36.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JORDAN HOEFT, Owes Student Debt:
So, I told
them, almost as a joke, I said,
I can either

38:36.414 --> 38:37.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
